The estimated cost to  Germany  from
exiting nuclear power and deploying alternative energy sources
will be at least 335 billion euros ($486 billion), Die Welt
reported, citing a study by the  Prognos  institute.  The cost includes expanding the capacity for alternative
power and adding to network infrastructure, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story: Ragnhild Kjetland in
Frankfurt at   rkjetland@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
